==English==

===Etymology===
From the larger expression “It’s the final straw that breaks the camel’s back”.
  
===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[final]] [[straw]]|-}}

# {{slang}} A small addition to a burden which causes it to exceed the capacity.  
#: ''That’s the '''final straw'''; it’s a petty demand but I’m already under too much work.  I quit!''

